				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: non-bard question (beastlord)<a name="9184"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Jul 16 03 12:26 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Easy answer...DON'T make an ogre.
<br />

<br />
Spend 10k on twink gear, and 50k on an illusion item
<br />

<br />
Or...
<br />

<br />
Spend 60k on twink gear, and play the race you want.
<br />

<br />
Not a hard decision.
<br />

<br />
The time and money that would go into changing the race of a beastlord would be FAR more than the time it would take to get gear that would negate the stat differences and thensome.  All beastlord races start with approx. the same TOTAL starting stats, ogres just have more str and sta, and less everything else.  Personally I think that Iksar make the best beastlords by far, having innate regen and innate AC bonus, and can forage.  Only trolls have regen besides iksar, but they lack the small size and ac bonuses of iksar.
<br />

<br />
My level 54 iksar monk has about 160str/sta/agl/dex unbuffed, and were he a beastlord, he would have about 200 to all those self buffed.  An ogre with the same gear would have 225str and 225sta, while having less AGL and Dex, and about 100 less AC.
<br />

<br />
If the looks of Iksar dont work for her, vah shir are second best, then troll/barb.  Ogre's low wis/dex/agl makes them dead last as far as beastlord races imo.
<br />

<br />
Choosing a race you dont like based solely on stats will make for a character that you will not enjoy.  Pick the race you like best, even if only for looks, as stats mean nothing later in the game.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
